posts.cooked:
We are trying to set up April Tags with PhotoVision, we configured the pi and everything, and the GUI works great, with live feed from the usb camera.

But when we tried to get the data to our code, following the code instructions from the PV docs we ran into a problem.

Initially we had a filler for the cameraName parameter in the PhotonCamera constructor, but when we went ahead and switchred the filler to the actual camera name as shown in the GUI (Microsoft lifecam HD-3000), the code immediately crashed with an ArrayOutOfBoundsException.

The Error resaulted from somewhere in the PhotonLib, and not from our code.

We tried to change the camera name in the gui and the code  to somthing shorter, and the same thing happened.

Any ideas why that would happen, abd how to fix it?

posts.name: Chris Gerth
posts.cooked:
A common cause of that symptom is forgetting to check hasTargets() before using a target in a result:

image 1027×800 33.3 KB

image 1027×800 33.3 KB

image 1027×800 33.3 KB

However, if you have a github repo or even just a zip file with your complete codebase, or the exact full text of the error, that would definitely help folks debug with you.

The reason is that there are many things which could cause the symptom you described. Working only off of the description, the best anyone could do is guess at root cause (as I did above). However, the full codebase or error text contains additional context and information (library versions, file names and line numbers, etc.) which open the potential for someone to prove the symptom is generated by a particular root cause. Generally, this is a more effective debugging method than guess-and-check till the symptom disappears.

Some resources:

posts.name: Chris Gerth
posts.cooked:
I looked at your codebase, but I’m not certain how photonlib could be causing a problem.

The only usage of the limelight singleton class that I found was in this comment . From inspection I’m not seeing anywhere else that photonlib is getting called.

Furthermore, INSTANCE is going to be Null here . I expect this to cause issues, but not an out-of-bounds array access.

Let us know if you need further help debugging. I’d recommend the following procedure to get help as quickly as possible:

Reproduce the issue

commit, push, and tag the exact code that the issue can be reproduced with.

Copy the exact text from the complete error message, including full stack trace and any preceding warnings. Reference wpilib’s docs on how to interpret the stack trace - the goal is to understand not just which line of code in photonlib is triggering the issue, but also the context within your code where it was called from, and any preceding warnings.

Grab a screenshot of the photonvision coprocessor’s settings page, which includes detailed info about the version of software, hardware, and network configuration.

Post back here with the info from 2, 3, and 4
